---
layout: layouts/default
title: Books
metaTagline: A list of books that I'm reading or have finished.
---

<p class="mb-4">
  {{ metaTagline }} Read about how I created this page in
  <a href="/posts/2025/creating-a-books-page">this blog post</a>.
</p>

<p class="mb-4 italic">Last updated: {{ books.lastUpdated | dateByFormat("MMMM d, y") }}</p>

<div class="my-8">
  <h2 class="my-4 flex items-baseline justify-between gap-x-4 text-lg font-bold" id="current">
    Currently Reading
    <span class="text-sm">{{ books.current.length }} book{%- if books.current.length > 1 -%}s{%- endif -%}</span>
  </h2>
  <div class="grid justify-around gap-6 [grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,120px)]">
    {%- for book in books.current %}
      <div class="flex flex-col justify-end gap-y-1">
        <a href="{{ book.goodreadsLink }}">
          {% set alt -%}Cover of {{ book.title }} by {{ book.author }}{%- endset %}
          {% set title -%}{{ book.title }} by {{ book.author }}{%- endset %}
          {% image book.coverUrl, alt, title, ["120"], "object-fit b-2 hover:rounded hover:outline hover:outline-4 hover:outline-blue-600 dark:hover:outline-yellow-500", book.goodreadsId %}
        </a>
      </div>
    {%- endfor -%}
  </div>
</div>

<div class="my-8">
  <div class="my-4 flex flex-wrap items-baseline justify-between">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-bold" id="finished">Finished Reading</h2>
    <span class="text-sm">üéß = audiobook ‚≠ê = really liked it</span>
  </div>

  {%- set years = books.read | getBookDateReadYears %}
  {%- for year in years %}
    {%- set subBooks = books.read | booksByYear(year) | sortDateByKey("dateRead", "desc") -%}
    <div class="mb-8">
      <h3 class="my-3 flex items-baseline justify-between gap-x-4 font-bold" id="{{ year }}">
        {{ year }}
        <span class="text-sm">{{ subBooks.length }} book{%- if subBooks.length > 1 -%}s{%- endif -%}</span>
      </h3>

      <div class="grid justify-around gap-6 [grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,120px)]">
        {%- for book in subBooks %}
          <div class="flex flex-col justify-end gap-y-1">
            <a href="{{ book.goodreadsLink }}">
              {% set alt -%}Cover of {{ book.title }} by {{ book.author }}{%- endset %}
              {% set title -%}{{ book.title }} by {{ book.author }}{%- endset %}
              {% image book.coverUrl, alt, title, ["120"], "object-fit b-2 hover:rounded hover:outline hover:outline-4 hover:outline-blue-600 dark:hover:outline-yellow-500", book.goodreadsId %}
            </a>
            <div class="flex flex-row items-center justify-between text-xs">
              <span>{{ book.dateRead | dateByFormat("MMM y") }}</span>
              <span>
                {%- if book.binding === 'audiobook' %}
                  üéß
                {%- endif %}
                {%- if book.rating > 3 %}
                  ‚≠ê
                {%- endif %}
              </span>
            </div>
          </div>
        {%- endfor -%}
      </div>
    </div>
  {%- endfor %}
</div>

<div class="my-8">
  <h2 class="my-4 text-lg font-bold" id="tbr">To Be Read</h2>
  <p class="mb-4">I'll definitely get around to reading those ADHD books one day...</p>
  <details>
    <summary>List of books</summary>
    <ul>
      {%- for book in books.tbr | sortByKey("title") %}
        <li class="my-2">
          <a class="font-bold" href="{{ book.goodreadsLink }}">{{ book.title }}</a>
          {{ book.author }}
        </li>
      {%- endfor -%}
    </ul>
  </details>
</div>

<div class="my-8">
  <h2 class="my-4 text-lg font-bold" id="dnf">Did Not Finish</h2>
  <p class="mb-4">
    While there's usually no specific reason why I choose not to finish a book, generally it comes down to "just
    couldn't get into it".
  </p>
  <details>
    <summary>List of books</summary>
    <ul>
      {%- for book in books.dnf | sortByKey("title") %}
        <li class="my-2">
          <a class="font-bold" href="{{ book.goodreadsLink }}">{{ book.title }}</a>
          {{ book.author }}
        </li>
      {%- endfor -%}
    </ul>
  </details>
</div>
